# Product UI Rules

- This is a toC product. UI copy should be minimal and user-facing.
- Do not use emoji anywhere in product UI, documentation updates, or commit text.
- Do not use gradients in UI styles, including Tailwind gradient utilities, CSS `linear-gradient`, `radial-gradient`, or similar background effects.
- Use a black, white, and gray palette by default. Do not introduce blue or other accent colors unless the user explicitly asks for them.
- Prefer solid neutral surfaces, clear spacing, strong typography, and subtle shadows.
- Do not add explanatory engineering copy to the interface.
- Avoid splitting simple content into many cards. Use cards only when they improve hierarchy.
- Cards must not use borders.
- Avoid decorative hover motion on display surfaces. Hover states should be subtle and functional.
- For copyable text or tags, hover should only use `cursor: pointer`; do not add decorative hover motion or color changes.
- Use existing maintained UI components or packages first. Implement custom UI only when no suitable component exists or the implementation is very small.
- Avoid unnecessary action buttons. Inputs should auto-update outputs when the interaction is obvious.
- For timestamp text conversion, preserve the original text layout and mark converted timestamp positions inline.
